<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-240-304 </DOCNO><DOCID>09 834 531</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Jan 21 1991 v8 n3 p13(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MasterCard project aims to cut net costs; firm plans todecentralize some operations and phase out IBM minis for lesscostly equipment.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brown, Jim.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>MasterCard International Inc is decentralizing some of its creditcard operations in order to reduce network costs and improvedisaster recovery procedures.andP;  The Project Omni plan will alsomigrate network nodes at member banks from its IBM minicomputersto a more flexible line of computers, possibly Unix-based, thatwill lower costs of linking to the network for member banks.andP;  Thecosts of MasterCard's clearing and settlement application will belowered by off-loading daily credit card clearing and settlementtasks from leased IBM 3090 mainframes to five minicomputers on itsBanknet credit card authorization network.andP;  Decentralizing theseoperations also improves the company's disaster recovery plans byeliminating the possibility of a single mainframe bringing downthe whole network.andP;  MasterCard is considering outsourcing most ofits network operations.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Mastercard International Inc. (Planning).andO;Topic:     DecentralizationCredit AuthorizationDisaster PlanningNetworksCost Reduction.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>